ZH: 我爷爷被诊断出患有肿瘤。
EN: My grandfather has been diagnosed with a tumor.
ZH: 许多人害怕得知他们身体上出现了肿瘤。
EN: Many people fear finding out they have a tumor.
ZH: 这种肿瘤需要做手术去除。
EN: This type of tumor needs to be surgically removed.
ZH: 在早期发现肿瘤可以提高治愈的机会。
EN: Discovering a tumor early can increase chances of cure.
ZH: 肿瘤可以通过化疗、放疗或手术进行治疗。
EN: Tumors can be treated with chemotherapy, radiation therapy, or surgery.
ZH: 他的肿瘤通过放疗后开始缩小。
EN: His tumor started shrinking after radiation therapy.
ZH: 肿瘤可能是恶性的。
EN: The tumor could be malignant.
ZH: 她需要进一步的检查以排除肿瘤的可能性。
EN: She needs further examination to rule out the possibility of a tumor.
ZH: 肿瘤研究有助于寻找治疗癌症的新方法。
EN: Tumor research helps in finding new ways to treat cancer.
ZH: 这种肿瘤可能是良性的并不需要紧急治疗。
EN: This type of tumor might be benign and not require urgent treatment.
ZH: 他的肿瘤在今年增长了20%。
EN: His tumor has grown by 20% this year.
ZH: 清除肿瘤需要一次大规模手术。
EN: Removing the tumor requires a major surgery.
ZH: 她感到非常紧张因为她怀疑自己患有肿瘤。
EN: She feels extremely anxious because she suspects she has a tumor.
ZH: 病人通过化验获知他拥有一个新的肿瘤。
EN: The patient found out about a new tumor through a test.
ZH: 肿瘤可能会扩散到其他器官。
EN: The tumor might spread to other organs.
ZH: 她的手术非常成功，肿瘤已经被完全切除。
EN: Her surgery was very successful, and the tumor has been completely removed.
ZH: 肿瘤的大小会决定治疗的方式。
EN: The size of the tumor determines the treatment approach.
ZH: 婴儿的肿瘤需要及时治疗。
EN: The baby's tumor needs to be treated promptly.
ZH: 他感到很难过，因为听到他朋友患有一个不治之症的肿瘤。
EN: He feels sad upon hearing that his friend has an incurable tumor.
ZH: 这种肿瘤的存活率通常很低。
EN: The survival rate for this type of tumor is usually low.
